 God would receive her soul and grant her eternal rest. Recall  that the deceased was commissioned into NAF in September 2017 after being a member of Nigerian Defence Academy (NDA) Regular Course 64. Arotile was a very confident and courageous young officer — Air Chief By Kingsley Omonobi – Abuja It has emerged that Flying Officer Tolulope Arotile died when her car had was hit by that of a former classmate, who was reversing to greet her. When the Nigerian Air Force (NAF)… July 15, 2020 In "News" As the country grapples to  come to terms with the shocking news of the death of the first female combat helicopter pilot in the Nigeria, Flying Officer Tolulope Arotile, Tuesday,  commemorations have continued to pour in as President Muhammadu Buhari commended her bravery in the field to protect the country… July 16, 2020 In "News" By Kingsley Omonobi , Johnbosco Agbakwuru & Tordue Salem As the country grapples to come to terms with the shocking news of the death of the first female combat helicopter pilot in Nigeria, Flying Officer Tolulope Arotile, Tuesday,  eulogies have continued to pour in as President Muhammadu Buhari commended her… July 15, 2020 In "News"